Definition.WordDefinition: well endowed adj : having plentiful supplies of a resource; "Brazil is well endowed with coffee"

well-endowed adj : (of a woman's body) having a large bosom and pleasing curves; "Hollywood seems full of curvaceous blondes"; "a curvy young woman in a tight dress" [syn: {bosomy}, {busty}, {buxom}, {curvaceous}, {curvy}, {full-bosomed}, {sonsie}, {sonsy}, {voluptuous}]
